Filtering Data Using WHERE, AND, OR, LIKE 


1 .The WHERE Clause

Example
SELECT * 
FROM students
WHERE age = 20;
 > Returns only students whose age is 20.

2 .Using AND
SELECT * 
FROM students
WHERE age = 20
AND course = 'BCA';
> Returns students who are 20 years old AND enrolled in BCA.

3 . Using OR 
SELECT * 
FROM students
WHERE course = 'BCA'
OR course = 'BTech';
> Returns students enrolled in BCA OR BTech.

4 .The LIKE Operator

Wildcards
Symbol	Meaning
%	Any number of characters
_	Exactly one character
Starts With
SELECT * 
FROM students
WHERE name LIKE 'A%';
>  Names starting with A

Ends With
SELECT * 
FROM students
WHERE name LIKE '%n';
> Names ending with n

Contains
SELECT * 
FROM students
WHERE name LIKE '%ar%';
> Names containing "ar"

Fixed Length Pattern
SELECT * 
FROM students
WHERE name LIKE 'R___';
>  Names starting with R and exactly 4 letters

5 .Combining AND & OR 
SELECT *
FROM students
WHERE (course = 'BCA' OR course = 'BTech')
AND age >= 20;
> Returns students in BCA or BTech who are at least 20 years old.

6 . Real-World Example
SELECT name, age, course
FROM students
WHERE age BETWEEN 18 AND 22
AND name LIKE '%a%';
> Students aged 18â€“22 whose name contains 'a'




